 consumer culture, and late capitalism on the other. The result is a powerful analysis of the intersection of conflict and consumerism in a world where governance is increasingly structured by brand ideology and wars sold as humanitarian interventions.   Full of rich, unforgettable ethnographic stories, Guerrilla Marketing is a stunning and troubling analysis of the mediation of global conflict.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aCounterinsurgencyzColombia. 0aInsurgencyzColombia. 0aMass media and peacezColombia. 0aMass media and warzColombia. 0aPropagandazColombia. 4aColombia. 4aFARC. 4aLatin America. 4abranding. 4acounterinsurgency. 4ademobilization. 4amarketing. 4amilitarism. 4apostconflict and peace building policy. 4apropaganda. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226590783423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226590783.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles